author: Takashi Nakamichi
title: 5-Yr JGBs Lowest Tender Price Seen at 100.22
text:
[Dow Jones] A lowest accepted price of around 100.22 is likely in today’s auction of five-year Japanese government bonds, traders say. The result is due 0345 GMT. The latest issue reopens the previous No. 125 issue carrying a coupon of 0.1%. “There is little concern about the five-year auction” with demand being solid, says Kazuhiko Sano, chief bond strategist at Tokai Tokyo Securities.
Write to Takashi Nakamichi at takashi.nakamichi@wsj.com...
